02:52.240 --> 02:55.809
[ Drill whirs ]

02:55.843 --> 03:00.614
[ Glass shatters ]
Look out! Watch out!

03:00.648 --> 03:01.815
Help!

03:01.849 --> 03:03.617
-Adam?!
-Oh, my God!

03:03.651 --> 03:05.219
Adam?!

03:05.253 --> 03:08.356
Somebody call 911!

03:08.389 --> 03:10.558
Oh, my God!

03:10.591 --> 03:14.828
I'm a doctor, let me take
a look. Let me take a look.

03:14.862 --> 03:16.297
His jugular vein's
been cut.

03:16.330 --> 03:17.331
Does anyone have
a clean cloth?

03:17.365 --> 03:18.332
Please. Someone!

03:18.366 --> 03:19.800
I have a fresh change
of clothes in my bag.

03:19.833 --> 03:20.734
That's great.

03:20.768 --> 03:30.744
**

03:30.778 --> 03:33.281
You're killing him.

03:33.314 --> 03:35.015
I'm saving his life.
He was bleeding out.

03:35.048 --> 03:36.917
N-- You have it in
the wrong place.

03:36.950 --> 03:38.752
I think I remember
enough of Anatomy 101

03:38.786 --> 03:40.254
to know where
the jugular vein is.

03:40.288 --> 03:42.490
You would be in the right place
if he were an adult.

03:42.523 --> 03:44.458
He's not an adult.
He is a boy.

03:44.492 --> 03:46.727
Which means you're also putting
pressure on his trachea.

03:46.760 --> 03:50.831
Which means he's not
currently breathing.

03:50.864 --> 03:53.767
You have to put
the pressure higher up.

03:53.801 --> 03:57.505
**

03:57.538 --> 03:58.906
There.
[ Gasps ]

03:58.939 --> 04:00.941
-Oh.
-Oh!

04:00.974 --> 04:09.683
**

04:09.717 --> 04:12.686
Some glass.
He'll be fine.

04:12.720 --> 04:14.422
Who are you?

04:14.455 --> 04:16.824
Hello.
I'm Dr. Shaun Murphy.

04:16.857 --> 04:17.991
I'm a surgical resident

04:18.025 --> 04:20.328
at San Jose
St. Bonaventure Hospital.

04:20.361 --> 04:23.331
-- Captions by VITAC --

04:23.364 --> 04:26.033
**

04:31.872 --> 04:35.075
Autism -- a mental condition
characterized by difficulty

04:35.108 --> 04:39.413
in communicating and using
language and abstract concepts.

04:39.447 --> 04:40.914
That's the definition.

04:40.948 --> 04:43.384
Does it sound like
I'm describing a surgeon?

04:43.417 --> 04:45.486
He's not Rain Man.

04:45.519 --> 04:47.955
He's high functioning, he's
capable of living on his own,

04:47.988 --> 04:50.558
capable of managing
his own affairs.

04:50.591 --> 04:52.526
"High functioning"?

04:52.560 --> 04:54.728
Is that our
new hiring standard?

04:54.762 --> 04:55.929
If it were,
you wouldn't be here.

04:55.963 --> 04:59.099
I'm sorry. Is this
really necessary? Really?

04:59.132 --> 05:01.535
A special meeting
of the Board of Directors --

05:01.569 --> 05:03.671
as much as I love you all --

05:03.704 --> 05:06.073
questioning one of
my hiring decisions?

05:06.106 --> 05:08.409
Did you bother to look up
the definition of "President"

05:08.442 --> 05:09.810
while you were skimming
the dictionary?

05:09.843 --> 05:12.746
You're hiring him to be
a surgical resident --

05:12.780 --> 05:15.416
my department --
over my objections.

05:15.449 --> 05:17.718
Marcus, stop making
everything so personal.

05:17.751 --> 05:18.919
I made it personal?

05:18.952 --> 05:20.554
You've wanted his job
since day one.

05:20.588 --> 05:21.755
Everyone in this room
knows that.

05:21.789 --> 05:24.091
And, Aaron, yes,
this is your hospital.

05:24.124 --> 05:24.925
But the money it takes to run it

05:24.958 --> 05:26.860
comes from
the Foundation I control.

05:26.894 --> 05:29.663
So let's all
play nice, shall we?

05:29.697 --> 05:31.732
Stop acting like you're stunned
that you're standing there.

05:31.765 --> 05:33.000
You tried to slip one past us.

05:33.033 --> 05:36.437
I vetted him like I would
any other candidate.

05:36.470 --> 05:38.071
And you genuinely thought
that this Board

05:38.105 --> 05:40.007
wouldn't reasonably
have any doubts about

05:40.040 --> 05:44.445
hiring a surgeon who's been
diagnosed with autism?

05:44.478 --> 05:46.380
So justify your decision.

05:46.414 --> 05:48.782
[ Sighs ]

05:48.816 --> 05:51.919
I met Shaun Murphy
when he was 14 years old.

05:51.952 --> 05:54.522
I was living in Wyoming
at the time.

05:54.555 --> 05:58.459
He was, and he still is,
an extraordinary young man.

05:58.492 --> 06:02.596
Yes, he has autism, but he also
has savant syndrome --

06:02.630 --> 06:04.998
genius-level skills
in several areas.

06:05.032 --> 06:08.802
He has almost perfect recall.
He has spatial intelligence.

06:08.836 --> 06:12.740
And he sees things
and analyzes things in ways

06:12.773 --> 06:14.742
that -- that are
just remarkable.

06:14.775 --> 06:17.778
In ways that we can't
even begin to understand.

06:17.811 --> 06:20.414
Those are assets.
Undeniable assets

06:20.448 --> 06:23.451
for any doctor,
particularly a surgeon.

06:25.886 --> 06:28.822
You've known him
since he was 14?

06:28.856 --> 06:30.991
You care about him.
He's like a son to you.

06:31.024 --> 06:34.127
Dr. Andrews, your wife is gonna
be very upset with you.

06:34.161 --> 06:35.963
If you're trying to turn this
into a nepotism case,

06:35.996 --> 06:38.732
we're gonna have to fire her
idiot nephew from bookkeeping.

06:38.766 --> 06:41.201
[ Laughter ]

06:41.234 --> 06:45.706
[ Woman speaking
indistinctly on P.A. ]

06:45.739 --> 06:46.874
Hey!

06:46.907 --> 06:48.108
Sorry. You seen Claire?

06:48.141 --> 06:49.443
Would you turn off
the light?

06:49.477 --> 06:50.578
Sure. You seen Claire?

06:50.611 --> 06:52.780
Why? Would you
turn off the light?

06:52.813 --> 06:54.582
Melendez wants
to operate on 104,

06:54.615 --> 06:56.584
but Claire hasn't gotten
informed consent.

06:56.617 --> 06:58.986
And she's ignoring her page.
You seen her?

06:59.019 --> 07:01.054
No. Now go away
and turn off the light.

07:01.088 --> 07:03.857
Sure.

07:03.891 --> 07:06.994
[ Scoffs ]

07:07.027 --> 07:10.230
[ Woman giggling ]

07:10.263 --> 07:12.032
They need you to, um...

07:12.065 --> 07:14.067
[ Laughs ] I heard.

07:16.236 --> 07:18.005
Oh, she's such a bitch.

07:18.038 --> 07:19.206
[ Laughs ]

07:19.239 --> 07:21.141
No.

07:21.174 --> 07:23.010
She just doesn't like you.

07:23.043 --> 07:26.747
Hmm.

07:26.780 --> 07:28.482
It's kind of silly,
isn't it?

07:28.516 --> 07:31.585
Um, maybe.

07:31.619 --> 07:32.853
To say for sure,
I'd need to know

07:32.886 --> 07:34.588
what it is
you're talking about.

07:34.622 --> 07:35.956
Us.

07:35.989 --> 07:39.192
Ah. Hmm.
Not silly at all.

07:39.226 --> 07:40.894
Quite a bit of fun,
actually.

07:40.928 --> 07:44.197
I meant that we're hiding it.
Our relationship.

07:44.231 --> 07:47.868
Hmm. Well...

07:47.901 --> 07:51.672
Jared, we don't
have a relationship.

07:51.705 --> 07:54.241
We have sex.

07:54.274 --> 07:57.511
But, if you want
to tell people

07:57.545 --> 08:03.116
that you're screwing me,
go for it.

08:03.150 --> 08:05.152
**

08:05.185 --> 08:08.255
[ Woman speaking
indistinctly on P.A. ]

08:08.288 --> 08:18.265
**

08:18.298 --> 08:27.140
**

08:27.174 --> 08:29.276
The veins in the boy's
left arm are popping.

08:29.309 --> 08:30.611
Is that bad?

08:30.644 --> 08:31.779
I-I don't see.

08:31.812 --> 08:33.246
Intrathoracic pressure.

08:33.280 --> 08:35.115
No, his chest is rising.
He's breathing.

08:35.148 --> 08:38.619
No, the -- the chest
is moving paradoxically.

08:38.652 --> 08:40.287
The left lung
is in distress.

08:47.795 --> 08:51.164
Yes.

08:51.198 --> 08:57.605
Who here has a sharp knife,
blade five inches or longer?

08:57.638 --> 08:58.839
Nobody?

08:58.872 --> 09:00.641
You should start
artificial respiration.

09:00.674 --> 09:03.276
He's going to stop
breathing very soon.

09:03.310 --> 09:07.681
**

09:07.715 --> 09:09.817
-I feel fine.
-Dr. Melendez would like

09:09.850 --> 09:11.985
to do the surgery today.

09:12.019 --> 09:15.122
You need bypass surgery
quite urgently.

09:15.155 --> 09:17.991
Would you please
sign the consent?

09:18.025 --> 09:19.292
No.

09:19.326 --> 09:20.694
You're scared.

09:20.728 --> 09:21.962
I-I'm not scared.

09:21.995 --> 09:22.730
Well, you should be.

09:22.763 --> 09:23.864
We're gonna
cut your chest open,

09:23.897 --> 09:27.267
we're gonna stop your heart,
repair it and restart it.

09:27.300 --> 09:29.870
Are you seriously telling me
that that doesn't scare you?

09:29.903 --> 09:31.939
I just want
a second opinion.

09:31.972 --> 09:35.909
Callum, yesterday,
your life was perfect.

09:35.943 --> 09:38.879
You were playing tennis,
you had a big anniversary.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.081
Today, you're lying
in a hospital bed

09:41.114 --> 09:43.316
trying to figure out
the best way to say goodbye,

09:43.350 --> 09:46.754
maybe forever,
to your teenage children.

09:46.787 --> 09:48.121
Why are you doing this?

09:48.155 --> 09:51.324
Because I can't
deal with lies.

09:51.358 --> 09:54.695
If you lie to me,
my answers won't help you.

09:54.728 --> 09:59.299
But, if you're scared,
I can help you.

09:59.332 --> 10:02.169
**

10:02.202 --> 10:03.737
I'm scared.

10:03.771 --> 10:05.706
Okay.

10:05.739 --> 10:09.009
[ Man speaking
indistinctly on P.A. ]

10:09.042 --> 10:11.178
-You can't be back here.
-Oh, I need a knife.

10:11.211 --> 10:12.345
Where do you
keep the knives

10:12.379 --> 10:14.047
people forget
they're traveling with?

10:14.081 --> 10:16.416
A knife?
Sure. Anything else?

10:16.449 --> 10:20.187
I do also need
a narrow six-foot tube

10:20.220 --> 10:21.789
and high-proof alcohol
and gloves

10:21.822 --> 10:23.891
and baggage-handling tape,
but I am going to get

10:23.924 --> 10:25.225
the alcohol from
the duty-free store

10:25.258 --> 10:27.127
and the tube from
the back of a soda machine.

10:27.160 --> 10:28.896
Well, I wish you
all the luck with that.

10:28.929 --> 10:29.897
But I'm not gonna
give you a knife.

10:29.930 --> 10:32.432
No, I need a knife.
It-It's -- It's very --

10:32.465 --> 10:35.903
There is a medical emergency.
There's a medical emergency.

10:35.936 --> 10:39.039
That one. That one, right near
the top, looks very sharp.

10:39.072 --> 10:40.173
Would you get it for me?

10:40.207 --> 10:41.809
No, I'm not gonna
give you a knife.

10:41.842 --> 10:45.045
I'll ask --
There's not the time.

10:45.078 --> 10:47.681
Weapon! Weapon!

10:49.049 --> 10:51.184
Move!
Get out of the way!

10:51.218 --> 10:53.854
[ Grunts ]

10:53.887 --> 10:56.023
Drop it.

10:56.056 --> 10:58.391
You idiot! You're lucky
we didn't just shoot.

10:58.425 --> 11:01.929
No! He's trying
to save my son's life.

11:01.962 --> 11:04.932
**

11:09.402 --> 11:11.304
You get that consent
on 104?

11:11.338 --> 11:13.040
Well, I made him a deal.

11:13.073 --> 11:16.176
He's got a meeting with
Dr. Max from psychiatry at 6:00,

11:16.209 --> 11:17.444
we'll get the consent
by 8:00,

11:17.477 --> 11:19.713
we can operate first thing
in the morning.

11:19.747 --> 11:21.181
You did pass anatomy,
right, Dr. Browne?

11:21.214 --> 11:22.850
His problem's in his heart,
not his head.

11:22.883 --> 11:24.752
He's not psychologically
ready for surgery.

11:24.785 --> 11:25.886
He will be. Soon.

11:25.919 --> 11:27.187
Well, he is
physically ready.

11:27.220 --> 11:29.189
So, get the consent.
We're prepping O.R. 6 now.

11:29.222 --> 11:31.491
Do I need to cite you
the 17 studies that show

11:31.524 --> 11:33.260
a correlation between
attitude and outcome

11:33.293 --> 11:34.294
in surgical patients?

11:34.327 --> 11:38.265
Do I need to remind you
that I am your superior?

11:38.298 --> 11:42.335
You do know what the opposite
of superior is, right?

11:42.369 --> 11:43.136
Subordinate. Doesn't --

11:43.170 --> 11:46.006
Sure. Subordinate.
Or...inferior.

11:46.039 --> 11:46.907
Either way.

11:46.940 --> 11:48.441
It doesn't mean I'm wrong.

11:48.475 --> 11:50.443
[ Scoffs ]
I suppose not.

11:50.477 --> 11:55.849
But it does mean you have
to act like you're wrong.

11:55.883 --> 11:57.217
He's panic stricken.

11:57.250 --> 11:59.252
Yesterday, he was
young and healthy.

11:59.286 --> 12:00.788
Today, he's mortal.

12:00.821 --> 12:03.456
Just give him a chance
to wrap his head around that.

12:03.490 --> 12:08.395
**

12:08.428 --> 12:11.031
Dr. Kalu?

12:11.064 --> 12:12.199
Do you think you can get me

12:12.232 --> 12:15.903
a signed informed
consent on 104?

12:15.936 --> 12:16.770
Of course.

12:16.804 --> 12:18.806
Thank you.

12:18.839 --> 12:21.441
**

12:21.474 --> 12:23.443
You think he's right?

12:23.476 --> 12:27.514
I think he's my boss.

12:27.547 --> 12:31.051
And if I have to choose
between my boss and...

12:31.084 --> 12:34.154
the woman I'm screwing,

12:34.187 --> 12:38.358
not much of a choice,
am I right?

12:38.391 --> 12:40.894
**

12:40.928 --> 12:44.131
Shaun: Excuse me.
Excuse me, please?

12:44.164 --> 12:50.938
**

12:50.971 --> 12:57.811
**

12:57.845 --> 13:04.451
**

13:04.484 --> 13:11.291
**

13:11.324 --> 13:18.098
**

13:18.131 --> 13:24.938
**

